- A glucose level greater than 140 indicates a potential treatable disease; 
- Blood pressure outside the range of 90 to 130 indicates a potential treatable disease; 
- The presence of a treatable disease is determined based on glucose levels and blood pressure, which are common indicators of health risks.

sql:
SELECT p.patient_id, p.address, p.phone_number
FROM patients p
WHERE p.blood_pressure > 130 AND p.pregnancies > 1;
